alcatelIND1WCCPMIB.description: This module describes an authoritative enterprise-specific Simple Network Management Protocol (SNMP) Management Information Base (MIB): The AlcatelIND1WCCPMIB is used to monitor the services for the WCCP (Web Cache Coordination Protocol). The right to make changes in specification and other information contained in this document without prior notice is reserved. alcatelIND1WCCPMIBConformance.name: alcatelIND1WCCPMIBConformance
alcatelIND1WCCPMIBConformance.description: Branch for WCCP application conformance information

alcatelIND1WCCPMIBGroups.name: alcatelIND1WCCPMIBGroups
alcatelIND1WCCPMIBGroups.description: Branch for WCCP application units of conformance

alcatelIND1WCCPMIBCompliances.name: alcatelIND1WCCPMIBCompliances
alcatelIND1WCCPMIBCompliances.description: Branch for WCCP application compliance statements

WccpServiceType.name: WccpServiceType
WccpServiceType.description: Indicates the type of WCCP service being used. standard - well known service is being used. dynamic - dynamic service is being used. unknown - cannot determine the type of service being used.

WccpVersion.name: WccpVersion
WccpVersion.description: Indicates the version of WCCP being used for a service. version1 - WCCP version 1 being used for the service. version2 - WCCP version 2 being used for the service. unknown - unknown version.

WccpServiceProtocolType.name: WccpServiceProtocolType
WccpServiceProtocolType.description: Indicates the type of protocol that a service group is defined for. tcp - WCCP service is identified by TCP protocol. udp - WCCP service is identified by UDP protocol.

WccpServiceMessageType.name: WccpServiceMessageType
WccpServiceMessageType.description: Indicates the type of message Exchanged used between The router and the cache-engines unicast - Unicast method is used for WCCP message exchange, i.e; the server and router exchange WCCP messages using the IP address of the server and router. multicast - Multicast method is used for WCCP message exchange, i.e; the server and router exchange WCCP messages using an IP multicast group address.

WccpServicePortType.name: WccpServicePortType
WccpServicePortType.description: Indicates the type of Ports being referred to in the Service Info Component in a WCCP message. source - The Ports in the Service Info Component refers to TCP/UDP source ports. destination - The Ports in the Service Info Component refers to TCP/UDP destination ports.

WccpOperState.name: WccpOperState
WccpOperState.description: The operational state of various WCCP entities 'outOfService' : The entity is out of service. 'inService' : The entity operates properly.

wccpServiceCount.name: wccpServiceCount
wccpServiceCount.description: The number of configured WCCP services.

wccpGlobalStatsReset.name: wccpGlobalStatsReset
wccpGlobalStatsReset.description: The variable will clear WCCP statistics for all the service groups.

wccpGlobalStatsMessageInvalid.name: wccpGlobalStatsMessageInvalid
wccpGlobalStatsMessageInvalid.description: This variable indicates the total no. of invalid WCCP Messages received.

wccpServiceTableEntry.name: wccpServiceTableEntry
wccpServiceTableEntry.description: A wccpServiceTable entry describes the WCCP service.

wccpServiceId.name: wccpServiceId
wccpServiceId.description: This variable indicates the WCCP's service id.

wccpServiceProtocol.name: wccpServiceProtocol
wccpServiceProtocol.description: This variable indicates the protocol type the WCCP Service is defined for

wccpServiceMessageType.name: wccpServiceMessageType
wccpServiceMessageType.description: This variable indicates the mode of WCCP message exchanges used between router and cache-engines (unicast/multicast).

wccpServicePortType.name: wccpServicePortType
wccpServicePortType.description: This variable indicates the type of TCP/UDP ports (source/destination) being referred to in Service Info Component in the WCCP Message.

wccpServiceAdminEnabled.name: wccpServiceAdminEnabled
wccpServiceAdminEnabled.description: This variable indicates WCCP's service status.

wccpServicePassword.name: wccpServicePassword
wccpServicePassword.description: This variable indicates the password for the WCCP service.

wccpServiceType.name: wccpServiceType
wccpServiceType.description: This variable indicates the WCCP service type.

wccpServiceVersion.name: wccpServiceVersion
wccpServiceVersion.description: This variable indicates the WCCP service version.

wccpServiceWebCacheCount.name: wccpServiceWebCacheCount
wccpServiceWebCacheCount.description: This variable show the number web caches currently active on the service.

wccpServiceReceiveId.name: wccpServiceReceiveId
wccpServiceReceiveId.description: This variable contains the current Receive ID from the router. This is incremented each time a WCCP message is sent.

wccpServiceChangeNumber.name: wccpServiceChangeNumber
wccpServiceChangeNumber.description: This variable contains the current Change Number. This is incremented each time there is a WCCP topology change.

wccpServicePrecedence.name: wccpServicePrecedence
wccpServicePrecedence.description: This variable indicates the priority of the Service. The lowest priority is 0, the highest is 255. Well known services have a priority of 240.

wccpServiceRowStatus.name: wccpServiceRowStatus
wccpServiceRowStatus.description: The object is used by a management station to create or delete the row entry in wccpServiceTable following the RowStatus textual convention.

wccpServicePortTableEntry.name: wccpServicePortTableEntry
wccpServicePortTableEntry.description: A wccpServicePortTable entry describes the WCCP service Ports.

wccpServicePortServiceId.name: wccpServicePortServiceId
wccpServicePortServiceId.description: This variable indicates the WCCP's service id.

wccpServicePortPortId.name: wccpServicePortPortId
wccpServicePortPortId.description: This variable indicates the WCCP's service Ports' id

wccpServicePortPortNum.name: wccpServicePortPortNum
wccpServicePortPortNum.description: This variable indicates the WCCP's service Ports' id Value.

wccpWebCacheTableEntry.name: wccpWebCacheTableEntry
wccpWebCacheTableEntry.description: A wccpWebCacheTable entry describes the status of a Web Cache.

wccpWebCacheServiceId.name: wccpWebCacheServiceId
wccpWebCacheServiceId.description: This variable indicates service id for this Web Cache.

wccpWebCacheIpAddressType.name: wccpWebCacheIpAddressType
wccpWebCacheIpAddressType.description: This variable IP address of the Web Cache. InetAddressType ipv4(1) is the only one supported at this time

wccpWebCacheIpAddress.name: wccpWebCacheIpAddress
wccpWebCacheIpAddress.description: This variable IP address of the Web Cache.

wccpWebCacheProtoVersion.name: wccpWebCacheProtoVersion
wccpWebCacheProtoVersion.description: This variable indicates the WCCP version supported by the Web Cache.

wccpWebCacheReceiveId.name: wccpWebCacheReceiveId
wccpWebCacheReceiveId.description: This variable contains the current Receive ID from the Web Cache.

wccpWebCacheChangeNum.name: wccpWebCacheChangeNum
wccpWebCacheChangeNum.description: This variable contains the current Change Number. This is incremented each time there is a WCCP topology change.

wccpWebCacheNumberOfRouters.name: wccpWebCacheNumberOfRouters
wccpWebCacheNumberOfRouters.description: This variable indicates how many WCCP routers the Web Cache is in contact with.

wccpWebCacheNumberOfWebCaches.name: wccpWebCacheNumberOfWebCaches
wccpWebCacheNumberOfWebCaches.description: This variable indicates how many Web Caches the Web Cache is in contact with.

wccpWebCacheState.name: wccpWebCacheState
wccpWebCacheState.description: This variable indicates the operational state of the Cache-Engine for a WCCP service.

wccpWebCacheConnectTime.name: wccpWebCacheConnectTime
wccpWebCacheConnectTime.description: This indicates the time at which the cache server was changed to usable state for the service.

wccpRouterTableEntry.name: wccpRouterTableEntry
wccpRouterTableEntry.description: A wccpRouterTable entry describes the various routers participating in a service group.

wccpRouterServiceId.name: wccpRouterServiceId
wccpRouterServiceId.description: This variable indicates service id for this Router.

wccpRouterIpAddressType.name: wccpRouterIpAddressType
wccpRouterIpAddressType.description: This variable indicates IP address type of the Router. InetAddressType ipv4(1) is the only one supported at this time

wccpRouterIpAddress.name: wccpRouterIpAddress
wccpRouterIpAddress.description: This variable indicates IP address of the Router.

wccpRouterProtoVersion.name: wccpRouterProtoVersion
wccpRouterProtoVersion.description: This variable indicates the WCCP version supported by the Router.

wccpRestrictVlanTable.name: wccpRestrictVlanTable
wccpRestrictVlanTable.description: Table of WCCP VLAN filter. Indicates on which VLANs redirection should take place

wccpRestrictVlanTableEntry.name: wccpRestrictVlanTableEntry
wccpRestrictVlanTableEntry.description: A wccpRestrictVlanTable entry describes the status of a VLAN restriction.

wccpRestrictVlanServiceId.name: wccpRestrictVlanServiceId
wccpRestrictVlanServiceId.description: This variable indicates WCCP's service id.

wccpRestrictVlanVlanId.name: wccpRestrictVlanVlanId
wccpRestrictVlanVlanId.description: This variable indicates a VLAN for redirection restrictions.

wccpRestrictVlanRowStatus.name: wccpRestrictVlanRowStatus
wccpRestrictVlanRowStatus.description: The object is used by a management station to create or delete the row entry in wccpServiceTable following the RowStatus textual convention.

wccpRestrictWebCacheTableEntry.name: wccpRestrictWebCacheTableEntry
wccpRestrictWebCacheTableEntry.description: A wccpRestrictWebCacheTable entry describes the status of a WCCP service.

wccpRestrictWebCacheServiceId.name: wccpRestrictWebCacheServiceId
wccpRestrictWebCacheServiceId.description: This variable indicates WCCP's service id.

wccpRestrictWebCacheIpAddressType.name: wccpRestrictWebCacheIpAddressType
wccpRestrictWebCacheIpAddressType.description: This variable is the IP address type of the Web Cache. Used with wccpRestrictWebCacheIpMask. InetAddressType ipv4(1) is the only one supported at this time

wccpRestrictWebCacheIpAddress.name: wccpRestrictWebCacheIpAddress
wccpRestrictWebCacheIpAddress.description: This variable is the IP address of the Web Cache. Used with wccpRestrictWebCacheIpMask.

wccpRestrictWebCacheIpMaskAddressType.name: wccpRestrictWebCacheIpMaskAddressType
wccpRestrictWebCacheIpMaskAddressType.description: This variable is the IP mask type of the IP Address.

wccpRestrictWebCacheIpMask.name: wccpRestrictWebCacheIpMask
wccpRestrictWebCacheIpMask.description: This variable is the IP mask of the IP Address.

wccpRestrictWebCacheRowStatus.name: wccpRestrictWebCacheRowStatus
wccpRestrictWebCacheRowStatus.description: The object is used by a management station to create or delete the row entry in wccpServiceTable following the RowStatus textual convention.

wccpRestrictPortTable.name: wccpRestrictPortTable
wccpRestrictPortTable.description: Table of WCCP Port filter. Indicates on which Ports redirection should not take place

wccpRestrictPortTableEntry.name: wccpRestrictPortTableEntry
wccpRestrictPortTableEntry.description: A wccpRestrictPortTable entry describes the status of a Port restriction.

wccpRestrictPortServiceId.name: wccpRestrictPortServiceId
wccpRestrictPortServiceId.description: This variable indicates WCCP's service id.

wccpRestrictPortIndex.name: wccpRestrictPortIndex
wccpRestrictPortIndex.description: This variable indicates a Port for redirection restrictions.

wccpRestrictPortRowStatus.name: wccpRestrictPortRowStatus
wccpRestrictPortRowStatus.description: The object is used by a management station to create or delete the row entry in wccpRestrictPortTable following the RowStatus textual convention.

wccpStatisticsTable.name: wccpStatisticsTable
wccpStatisticsTable.description: Table of WCCP traffic related Statistics.

wccpStatisticsTableEntry.name: wccpStatisticsTableEntry
wccpStatisticsTableEntry.description: A wccpStatisticsTableEntry entry describes the WCCP traffic related statistics for a service Group

wccpStatsServiceId.name: wccpStatsServiceId
wccpStatsServiceId.description: This variable indicates WCCP's service id.

wccpStatsMessagesReceived.name: wccpStatsMessagesReceived
wccpStatsMessagesReceived.description: This variable indicates the total no. of valid WCCP Messages Received by the Router for the service group.

wccpStatsMessagesTransmitted.name: wccpStatsMessagesTransmitted
wccpStatsMessagesTransmitted.description: This variable indicates the total no. of valid WCCP Messages transmitted by the Router for the service group.

wccpStatsMessagesDropped.name: wccpStatsMessagesDropped
wccpStatsMessagesDropped.description: This variable indicates the total no. of WCCP Messages dropped for the service group, as a result of the WCCP restrictions on Port/Vlan/Ip

wccpStatsPacketsRedir.name: wccpStatsPacketsRedir
wccpStatsPacketsRedir.description: This variable indicates the how many packet WCCP has redirected.

wccpStatsPacketsLowRedir.name: wccpStatsPacketsLowRedir
wccpStatsPacketsLowRedir.description: This variable indicates the how many packet WCCP has redirected - lower 32 bits.

wccpStatsPacketsDeniedRedir.name: wccpStatsPacketsDeniedRedir
wccpStatsPacketsDeniedRedir.description: This variable indicates the how many packets WCCP has denied to redirect.

wccpStatsAuthFailures.name: wccpStatsAuthFailures
wccpStatsAuthFailures.description: This variable indicates the count of how many WCCP packets resulted in authentication failure because of mismatch in the password used for the Service on the Router and a Cache-Engine.

wccpStatsReset.name: wccpStatsReset
wccpStatsReset.description: The object is used by a management station to reset the wccpStatistics info from this table

wccpTrapOperStatus.name: wccpTrapOperStatus
wccpTrapOperStatus.description: A change occured in the operational status of a wccp entity.

wccpTrapInfoOperStatus.name: wccpTrapInfoOperStatus
wccpTrapInfoOperStatus.description: The operational status of wccp, service or webcache.

wccpTrapInfoWebCacheIpAddr.name: wccpTrapInfoWebCacheIpAddr
wccpTrapInfoWebCacheIpAddr.description: The IP address of a Web Cache.

wccpTrapInfoEntityGroup.name: wccpTrapInfoEntityGroup
wccpTrapInfoEntityGroup.description: The entity group inside wccp management.

wccpFeatureGroup.name: wccpFeatureGroup
wccpFeatureGroup.description: Collection of objects for management of Web Cache Coordination

wccpServiceGroup.name: wccpServiceGroup
wccpServiceGroup.description: Collection of objects for management of WCCP services

wccpWebCacheGroup.name: wccpWebCacheGroup
wccpWebCacheGroup.description: Collection of objects for management of WCCP Web Caches

wccpRouterGroup.name: wccpRouterGroup
wccpRouterGroup.description: Collection of objects for management of WCCP Router

wccpRestrictVlanGroup.name: wccpRestrictVlanGroup
wccpRestrictVlanGroup.description: Collection of objects for management of WCCP Web Caches

wccpRestrictWebCacheGroup.name: wccpRestrictWebCacheGroup
wccpRestrictWebCacheGroup.description: Collection of objects for management of WCCP Web Caches

wccpRestrictPortGroup.name: wccpRestrictPortGroup
wccpRestrictPortGroup.description: Collection of objects for management of WCCP Web Caches

wccpStatisticsGroup.name: wccpStatisticsGroup
wccpStatisticsGroup.description: Collection of objects for management of WCCP SG's traffic statistics

wccpTrapsGroup.name: wccpTrapsGroup
wccpTrapsGroup.description: Collection of traps for management of WCCP

wccpOperStatusGroup.name: wccpOperStatusGroup
wccpOperStatusGroup.description: Collection of objects for WCCP OperStatus Notification.
